de.bioforscher.singa.structure.parser.pdb.structures

Class StructureParser.MultiParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bioforscher.singa.structure.parser.pdb.structures.StructureParser.MultiParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<Structure>
    Enclosing class:
    StructureParser

    public static class StructureParser.MultiParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<Structure>
    The MultiParser performs parsing of multiple structures from a single source. Using the Iterator pattern the structures can be parsed and processed individually. Each specified structure will be parsed lazily so parsing until a certain condition is met can be done without parsing unused structures. Additionally some speedups are provided parsing multiple structures. Every ligand is only parsed once, the first time it is encountered, afterwards it is stored as a LeafSkeleton that is completed with the the concrete atom positions for each new occurrence.
